{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00222254632/1930081801/0436.xml":{"full_text":"20\nWELLS FARGO\nI SEES TBADE\nr REVIVAL\nSAN FRANCISCO, Aug. 18\nRetail trade in California so far\n'.this year has fared better than\nin the nation as a whole, accord\ning to the current issue of the\nBusiness Outlook released today\nby the Wells Fargo Bank and\nUnion Trust Company. \u2018\u2022Business\nin the first 10 days of the month\nis reported equal to or better than\nthe corresponding period last year\nin many lines, notably women\u2019s\nclothing, shoes, hardware, furni\nture, groceries and mail order\nsales; less business than a year\n.ago is reported by department\nstores, men\u2019s clothing and dry\ngoods.\u201d y\nCommenting on this, Wells Far\ngo Bank Trust Company states:\n\u2018\u2018Department store business com\npared with a year ago shows a\ndecline of 7.6 per cent for July\nand of 3.7 per cent for the year\nto date, compared with national\ndeclines of 9 per cent and 5 per\ncent, respectively.\"\nOne of the bright spots in Cali\nfornia business is to be found in\nlife insurance sales. In this con\nnection, the Business Outlook\nsays:\n\u201cLife insurance business in\nthe State continues to show\nmarked improvement over even\nlast year\u2019s record totals; June\nsales were 17 per cent greater\nthan in June, 1929, bringing\nthe first half of this year 11\nper cent ahead of a year ago.\nThe California total of life in\nsurance sales in June was ex\nceeded only in New York, Penn\nsylvania and Illinois.\u201d\nCitrus crop returns this year\nare eminently satisfactory. Con\ncerning this industry the bank\nreports an average sized crop of\n10,920,000 boxes of Valencia\noranges is expected this year and\ncompared with the record-break\ning harvest of 17,500,000 boxes in\n1929. Quality is much better this\nyear than last. This fact, com\nbined with smaller supplies,\ncaused f. o. b. prices to average\n$5.87 a box during July against\n$2.35 a year ago and $5.87 in\n1928.\nBABSON SHOWS\nME PIMP\nOMAHA, Neb., Aug. 18 (IN.S.).\nBusines leaders of the Middle\nWest today were regarding with\noptimism tnhe prediction of a gen\neral business improvement made\nby Roger W. Babson.\nBabson said business in general\nthroughout the middle western\nstates will show marked improve\nment during the last quarter of\n1930. The economist also pre\ndicted a healthier agricultural\nsituation in the central area.\nThis was Babson\u2019s first public\nannouncement on the busies out\nlook since his forecast of'ap\nproaching depresion last Nov'ftn\nber, he said:\n\u201cThe farmer is practically\nr flat on his back out here and\nconditions are as bad right now\nv as they can get.\u201d\nEuropean countries have become\nworried and are now placing\norders after a long buying strike,\nhe said.\nThree Groups Plan\nTrips on the River\nThe Review and Herald Pub\nlishing Association will go to\nChapel Point on the Wilson Line\nsteamer City of Washington to\nmorrow. Messrs. Richmond and\nConard of the association will be j\nin charge. JVednesday the North\nern Athletic Club will go on the\nmoonlight ride.\nThe committee consists of\nGeorge P. Delaney, Charles\nGrier, Joseph Pritchi and Frank\nCarr. On Friday the Alpha Sig\nma Lambda, Psi Phi Chapter\nwill go down the river. J. S.\nHoover and J. W. Cooper are\nhandling the trip.\nNebraskans Enter\nNegro in Seat Race\nDr. John Andrew Singleton, a\ngraduate of the Howard Univer\nsity Dental School, was nominated\nas representative to the State\nLegislature of Nebraska from the\nNinth District during the pri\nmaries. Dr. Singleton scored a\nvictory over fellow aspirants, one\nwhite and one colored newspaper\nman. j\nHis popularity sent him as rep\nresentative to the Nebraska legis\nlature in 1928.\nDr, T, Edward Jones\nIs Legion Delegate\nDr. T. Edward Jones, of Freed\nmen\u2019s Hospital, and the James\nE. Walker Post. American Legion,\nwas named delegate to the na\ntional convention of the Ameri\ncan Legion which will be held at\nBoston, Mass., September 6,7, 8.\nJohn R. Anderson, of the James\nReese Europe Post, was named\nalternate.\nA \u00abar far ye\u00ab and va\u00ab* for the fam\nily can he purrhaaed for the price of\naew om. through today\u2019a Classified\np COMPLETE QUOTATIONS ON THE NEW YORK CURB MARKET\nQuotations Furnithad by W. B. Hibba A C\u00bb. by Diftct Wira from tho Exehongb\nN 1 I\n-Pro* Name and Not\nHigh Low Dividend Rato High Low 111* Ch'ga\nA\n109 k 105*-. Al Co of Am pf (6) '9k 109 k 109\u20191 k\nt Allegheny Gan... 4 4k 4k\nUh u Am Capital 8... 7\n8k 12k Am Cities Pwr B. s>> Hk 15k- h\n28* 20!< Am Com w A (10b I*4 21k 21*1\n37 17 Am Cynm B (1.60 19 19k 19H- It\n157 1(M Am Gas El (la 12 H 122 129 k\nJ9k 20k Am Superpr (1). 2 -lk 21k-\n15k 714 Am U&GCr Bvi 9k 9k 9\u00bb%+ *A\nI4\u2019g 6 An Post Fe (10%b, 8h B\u2018. 1\n161* 81 Ark Natl Gas A.. 91* 9S xk\nIt! 3'i\u2019 Asso Gas A Ufa).. 30k 014 30k\n6k 3\u2019s Asso Rayon 2k -k 2k\u2014 k\nk '4 Atl Fruit Sug.. k k H\n5 2k Atlas Util wr.. t 3 k\n.0 12' Aviation Cred.... 20k 19k 19k\u201c k\nB\n7k *k Bahia Corp pf... -k -k k+ k\n15k 6k Blue Ridge b\u00bb> 7k 7k- k\n44k Blue Rid cv pf (2} 43\u2019 .*k 39k\u2014 1\nisk 3\u2019 Brazil Trac (2)... 4k -4k 4k-\n69 54k Buckeye Pipe (4).. 5 55 55 h\n-6k 24k BuffNAEpf... 6k 26k -6k\nC\nk k Cam Co k k\n2* Carlb Synd Ik B Ik\u2014 k\n90 60 Cel of Am Ist pf. 60k 60k 60\nJk 3k Cana Marconi.... 4 4 4 k\n20 12 Celluloid Uk 19k 19k\n40k 25k Cent P S Del 31 31 31+3\nJ9k 19 Cent Sta El (40a). 21k 20k .1- k\n42k 25 Cn PSMd A (1%: 26 tbty -6 k\n25 17>. Chat Ph All nv.. 18k 18k 18k\n25k 171. Chat Nat Asso nv, 24 23k -3k\u201c k\n44k -4!. Cities Ser (30a)... -7k 27k 27k- k\n.1 5k Col Oil Gas vt< 'k 7 7J-.+ 1.,\n335 k 234 cSm Edison (8)... .92k -92\" -92k+ <k\n6k k Coml S war k ok *k\n19k Ilk Com Water 6% b. 13 B 13 k\n27k 15 Cons Aircraft.... J6k 16k 16\u2019.\u2014 k\n8k 3% Cons Copper M.. 4 4\nU 10 Con Laund 13 B 13 k\n17k 6 Cord Corp <k 7k 7k+ k\n20k 9 Corroon Rev... 9 9 9 k\n7k 5k Creole Petrol 5k 5k 5k k\nk k Cresson Gold (08), k k k+ k\n34\u20194 15 Crocker Wheeler. 17k 17k 17k+ k\n4k Ik 3ur Wright war.. Ik Ik Ik\nD\n8k 2k DeForest Rad.... 3k 3* 3k\n$900,0011 HAIN\nWEBS WEST\nCHICAGO, Aug. 18 (1.N.5.).\u2014\nFarmers throughout the Middle\nWest took heart today after week\nend rains which routed the\ndrought and promised to save\nmillions of dollars worth of crops.\nThe arid spell has been broken\nexcept in a few scattered sections\nin the com and cotton belts, ac\ncording to weather observers.\nFarmers in the vicinity of\nPeoria, Hl., hailed the .66 inch\nprecipitation as worth $500,000,\nstating that the corn crop has\nbeen saved. Sections of Kane\nand Dupage counties, Hl., received\nmore than three inches of rain\nfall over the week-end.\nLower Hlinois, Indiana, Wiscon\nsin, Minnesota, lowa and Nebraska\nalso reported rainfall which is\nexpected to revive the crops.\nRainfall records in the Middle-\nWpcf wpfp\nSpringfield, 111., 1.15 inches;\nDes Moines, .43; Keokuk, lowa.\n1.40; Valentine. Nebr.. 1.58;\nOmaha, .34; Terre Haute. Ind.,\n1.24; Evansville, Ind.. .96: Kan\nsas City, Mo., 1.69; St. Joseph,\nMo., 1.73; Springfield. Mo.. 2.23;\nDavenport, lowa, 1.; Fort Dodge,\nlowa, 1.18.\nConstruction Board\nTo Act on Credits\nThe working details of the plan\nrecently launched by the Allied\nConstruction Industries to sta\nbilize credit conditions in the\nconstructive industry by the co\noperative observance of stated\ncredit practices, are to be de\ncided tomorrow at a meeting here\nof the organization\u2019s board of di\nrectors, H. E. Foreman, secre\ntary of the board, announced\nyesterday.\nThe movement is intended to\nhelp the success of President\nHoover\u2019s plan to stabilize busi\nness through the acceleration of\nconstruction. The board consists\nof Edward J. Harding, of the As\nsociated General Contractors,\nFrank Dunning, of the National\nBuilders Supply Association, and\nEdward McDonnell, of the Con\ntracting Plasterers Association.\nSnake Attacks Man;\nHis Shoes Save Him\nLURAY, Va., Aug. 18.\u2014His\nripped up shoes kept as a mo\nmenta of a battle he waged with\na four-foot rattlesnake attest the\nnarrow escape from death yester\nday of A. G. Thomas, living in\nMadison county, 18 miles east of\nLuray.\nWhen Thomas first saw the\nsnake it was stretched on a board.\nThomas struck it with a piece of\nwood and the snake fastened it\nself to his shoes, its fangs buried\nin the leather.\nRescuers finally pulled the\nsnake loose when it was killed.\nW, B, Patterson Off\nOn Northern Jaunt\nW. B. Patterson, director of\nspecial activities in the District's\nschools, left today on a two-an i-a\nhalf-week automobile trip to Ni\nagara Falls and Thousand Is\nlands.\nPatterson is in charge of the\nsummer schools, which concluded\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMES\n1930 to Be a Fixed Trust\nYear, Banker Says\nNineteen-thirty promises to be\na fixed trust year, as 1929 was\na management trust year, in the\nopinion of John Newey, executive\nvice president of the Standard\nAmerican Corporation. He esti\nmated that by the end of this\nyear fixed trust shares sold the\npublic would be in excess of\n$375,000,000.\nMr. Dewey said:\n\u201cDuring the early part of\n1930, when it was difficult to\nsell any kind of stock, \u201cthere\nbegan to develop a very notice\nable public acceptance for fixed\ntrust shares. New fixed trust\nshares began to appear on every\nhand and most of them seemed\nto do very well. It is esti\nmated that the amount of fixed\ntrust sold during the past 18\nmonths is in excess of $275,-\n000,000, and by the end of the*\nyear it is not unlikely that this\nfigure will be increased by at\nleast another $100,000,000.\n\u201cDuring the first half of 1930\nthe fixed trust has largely sup\nplanted the management type\nof trust in public interest.\nHowever, there appears to be\nlittle prospect that the value\nof these shares distributed will\nequal the phenomenal record\nof management trusts last year\nwhen more than $2,000,000,000\nwas absorbed by the public.\n\"Although the classification\nof \u2018investment trusts* has been\nloosely used to cover both the\nmanagement and fixed type of\ntrust\u2014they are in reality en\ntirely different in principle,\nand the fixed trust is some\nthing entirely new in financial\nannals. The development of\nthe holding corporation during\nLOim\nDHOP MOTION\nThe Great Northern and North\nern Pacific Railroads today asked\nthe Interstate Commerce Com\nmission to dismiss the motion of\nthe Minnesota Railroad and Ware\nhouse Commission and similar\nmotions of the Railroad Com\nmissions of Montana, Illinois,\nNorth Dakota, Wisconsin, Wash\nington and Oregon, to reopen the\nGreat Northern Pacific unifica\ntion case.\nThey pointed out that the re\nopening of the case at this time\nwould serve no useful purpose,\nsince the commission has with\nheld the issuance of any order\npending submission of the two\nroads of -a supplemental plan\ncomplying with the four require\nments found by the Commission\nto be necessary in order that the\nproposed unification may be in\nthe public interest.\nWaynesboro Plans\nFor Better Airport\nSTAUNTON, Va., Aug. 18.\nSteps toward making the local\nlanding at Waynesboro, a class A\nairport have been undertaken by\nthe Waynesboro City Council.\nThe State Highway Department\nhas announced an appropriation\nof SI,OOO to be used to improve\nthe field, providing the city meets\ncertain requirements of lighting\nand grading. Except for light\ning, the field is said to be one of\nthe best in the State.\nt\u00bbM\u2014 Name ane\nHlah Law DlrMand Rata Rich Low lilt Ch\u2019wo\n9* j 3k Dat Aircraft 4k 4k 4k- k\n7 2k Durant i 2k 3\ne,4-\n117 k 70k Elac\u00df *8 6% b.. 78k 76k 76k- Ik\n85k 92k El BAS 6pr 95 95 95\n78k 28k El PA Lop war... 44 44 44 +3\n8k 6 Empire Corp 6k ,6k 6k 4 k\n2k Eng Gold Mjnea.. k k k+ k\nF\n2k \u2019i Fandango Corp.. k k k\n22k 15k Fiat Am retailk). 15k 15k 15k~ k\n3k k Fiat deb reta.... k k k- k\nMk 13\u2018j Fokker Urcr 18k 18 18 k\n38k 28 Ford of Can A 1 31 31 k\n23k 10k Ford Motor Ltd 21k 21k 21M- k\n17k 2k Fox Theater A.... 8k 8k 8k k\n24 6 Franklin Mfg.... 6 6 6 -10 k\nG\n14k 6k Gen Alloys (80)... 11 10 10-1\n4k 2h Gen Baking 2k 2k 2k\n29k 18k Gen Emp Corp... 18k 18k 18k- k\n37k 29 Gen Fireproof (2a) 29k 29k 29k\u201c k\n6 Ik Gold Seal new.... 2 2 2\n46k 15k Goldn Sea Tr <6%b 15k 15k 15k\n260 180 Gt A4P Tea n v(5), 200k 200k 200k\u201c 4k\n29k 22k Guenther-Law (2). 22k 22k 22k- Ik\nH\n14 8k Hecla Mining (1).. 8k 8k 8k\n7k 3 Helena Rubinatee, 3 3 3 k\n7 5 Hollinger Mines.. 5k 5k 5k- k\n14k 7 Hudson Bay 7k 7k 7k+ k\n15 8k Hygrade F00d.... 10 10 10\u20141\n1\n30 18k Im OU Can new (k 19k 19k 19k- k\n23 15k Insurance Sec (1.4 C 15k 15k 15k+ k\nIk k Intercont Pet..... k k k\u2014 k\n24 17k Internal Pet (1)... 18k 18k 18k- k\n46k 30k Int Super Pw (la). 33k 33k' 33k+ k\n9k' 3k Italian Sup deb rt., 4k 4k 4k+ k\nL\n12 3k Lakev Fdry -k 4k 4k\n25k 13k Lefco\u2019rt Rty (1.60a; 14k 14k 14k~ k\n50L 30 Lehigh CAN new Jk -Ik >lk\u201c 2k\n4k l\u2018a Leonard Oil Ik Ik Ik\n5 La Land 2k k \u2018-k+ h\nM\nIlk Marconi Inter '5%) 8k 8k 8k 1\n\u2018.h i Mavis Botl lk ik i\u2018.\u00ab\n82k r s l Mead Johnson s3a) Sik 82k 82k\u2014\nthe past few years has accus\ntomed the public to think of\ncorporations not only as busi\nness enterprises, but also as\ninvesting institutions, and .the\ndevelopment of management\ntrusts\u2014which 'are corporations\nwhose business is investing\u2014\nwas a natural and logical step.\nThe fixed trust, however, is\nessentially a plan of invest\nment\u2014supervised by a trust\ncompany\u2014rather than a busi\nness enterprise.\n\u201cIn brief, the fixed trust\nplan is simply to select a cer\ntain list of securities\u2014usually\nall common stocks\u2014and to in\nvite the public to buy shares in\na trust deposit composed of\nthese securities.\n\u201cWith the increasing develop\ni ment of the fixed trust idea,\nthe strength and conservatism\nof the sponsoring bankers is\nnow coming to become more\nand more of a sales factor,\njust as such sponsorship be\ncame an important factor last\nyear in the development of\nmanagement trusts. The secur\nity affiliate of one of the\nlarger Chicago metropolitan\nbanks and one of the more con\nservative Chicago bond houses\nhave recently sponsored the dis\ntribution of such a trust, and\nit is rumored that several im-\nI portant cid well-known Eastern\ninstitutions are about to enter\nthe field. Such sponsorship\nmay well bring about a popu\nlarity for fixed trust shares\nthat may eventually rival the\ngreat rise in management\ntrusts which took place last\nyear.\u201d\nON BOMS\nSTOPS NOV, 15\nBALTIMORE, Aug. 18.\u2014Ad\nvance allocation Saturday of Fed\neral road-aid funds to assist in\nallieviating conditions in drought\nridden States will have little, if\nany, effect in Maryland, it was\nsaid yesterday.\nThe money ordinarily would.\nnot have been available until\nJanuary 1. Os the $121,875,000\nallocated, Maryland\u2019s share would\nbe $1,051,714.\nMaryland\u2019s road construction\nstops on November 15 because of\nwinter weather conditions. The\nmoney will be of great benefit\nto Southern States, where con\nstruction is permissable through\nout the year, it was said.\nOslo Bonds Drawn,\nFirm Announces\nKuhn, Loeb <fc Co., as fiscal\nagents, are notifying holders of\nCity of Christiania, now Oslo,\n(Norway) municipal external\nloan of 1924 30-year 6 per cent\nsinking fund gold bonds, due\nSeptember 1, 1954, to the effect\nthat $40,000 principal amount of\nthe bonds have been drawn by\nlot for redemption on September\n1 at par. Bonds so drawn will\nbe paid upon presentation and\nsurrender, with subsequent cou\npons attached, at the offices of\nKuhn, Loeb Co., 52 William St.,\non and after September 1, after\nwhich date interest on the drawn\nbonds will cease.\nFM WatfwMf IMF\n-Pr\u00abv Nami and Mt\nHigb Low Dividend Rate High Low lilt C